ZH: 时间如流逝的河水，在我们指尖溜走。
EN: Time slips away like flowing river water through our fingertips.

ZH: 我们应该珍惜每一刻，因为逝去的时间再也无法回来。
EN: We should cherish every moment, for the time that has passed will never come back.

ZH: 我们感叹岁月的流逝，却忽略了珍惜当下。
EN: We lament the passing of time, yet we forget to appreciate the present.

ZH: 春去秋来，轮回不已，岁月流逝，岁月流逝。
EN: Spring gives way to autumn, the cycle never ends, time passes, time passes.

ZH: 逝者如斯夫，不舍昼夜。
EN: The passing of time is swift, without distinction between day and night.

ZH: 每一次呼吸，都是时间的流逝。
EN: Every breath we take is the passage of time.

ZH: 花开花落，一年又过去了，光阴荏苒，岁月如歌。
EN: Flowers bloom and wither, another year has passed, time flies by like a song.

ZH: 我感受到时间的流逝，仿佛脚下的沙漠逐渐被风吹净了。
EN: I can feel the passage of time, as if the desert under my feet is gradually being swept clean by the wind.

ZH: 流逝的时间是一场静默的教育，它在无声中教会我们珍惜。
EN: The passage of time is a silent education, teaching us to cherish in its silence.

ZH: 时光像流逝的细水一般，从指缝间悄然溜走。
EN: Time passes like flowing water, quietly slipping away between our fingers.

ZH: 时间的流逝是一场无情的旅行，无法停止，无法阻挡。
EN: The passage of time is a merciless journey that cannot be stopped or blocked.

ZH: 唯有留下回忆，才能与流逝的时间共鸣。
EN: Only by leaving behind memories can we resonate with the passing of time.

ZH: 日日如梭，岁月如流，时间从指尖流逝。
EN: Day after day, time flows like a river, slipping away from our fingertips.

ZH: 随着时间的流逝，我们慢慢长大，学会面对生活的起伏与挑战。
EN: With the passage of time, we gradually grow up and learn to face the ups and downs and challenges of life.

ZH: 不要抱怨时间的流逝，而是要努力让每一天都变得有意义。
EN: Don't complain about the passage of time, but strive to make every day meaningful.

ZH: 青春不再，时间的流逝让我们不禁感叹岁月易逝。
EN: Youth is no more, and the passing of time makes us sigh for the fleeting years.

ZH: 每一次与亲人的相聚，都时光的美好流逝。
EN: Every reunion with loved ones is a beautiful passage of time.

ZH: 月有阴晴圆缺，岁有春夏秋冬，流逝的时间给予生命无尽的变幻。
EN: The moon waxes and wanes, the seasons change, and the passing of time bestows endless transformations upon life.

ZH: 随着时间的流逝，我们逐渐明白什么是真正重要的东西。
EN: With the passage of time, we gradually understand what truly matters.

ZH: 时间的流逝如同无声的钟摆，只有在回首时才会发现它的存在。
EN: The passage of time is like a silent pendulum, its existence only revealed when we look back.
